{
    "publish_date": "2010-03-22T17:48:02.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT10M49S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "OSHO", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OSHO TALKS:  silence shared in words", 
            "dur": "6", 
            "start": "14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OSHO International Foundation presents", 
            "dur": "5", 
            "start": "24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Osho: Why is Communication so Difficult, Particularly between Lovers?", 
            "dur": "7", 
            "start": "30"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These discourses are the foundations of your meditation.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sitting with me in these discourses is nothing but creating more and more meditativeness in you.", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t speak to teach something; I speak to create something.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These are not lectures; these are simply a device for you to become silent. -- Osho", 
            "dur": "6", 
            "start": "49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why is communication so difficult,", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "particularly between lovers?", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "80"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Premda,", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "111.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "communication as such is difficult.", 
            "dur": "4.16", 
            "start": "117.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Of course it is more difficult between lovers.", 
            "dur": "4.96", 
            "start": "125.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But first you have to understand", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "136"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the general difficulty of communication.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Each mind", 
            "dur": "1.14", 
            "start": "146.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has been", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "152"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "conditioned by different parents, different teachers,", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "154"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "different priests, different politicians.", 
            "dur": "4.56", 
            "start": "159.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is a different world in itself.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when two minds try to communicate,", 
            "dur": "4.961", 
            "start": "173.739"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as far as the ordinary mundane things are concerned,", 
            "dur": "5.78", 
            "start": "180.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there is no difficulty.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "186.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the moment they start moving beyond things", 
            "dur": "4.18", 
            "start": "191.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into the world of concepts,", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "201.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "communication starts becoming more and more difficult.", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "207.779"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For example,", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "225.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gautam the Buddha", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "236.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "does not have any God", 
            "dur": "3.361", 
            "start": "242.739"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in his philosophy.", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "247.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He is far more", 
            "dur": "1.922", 
            "start": "259.578"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "free from God than even Friedrich Nietzsche.", 
            "dur": "5.75", 
            "start": "270.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "At least Friedrich Nietzsche", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "278"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "states that God is dead.", 
            "dur": "3.06", 
            "start": "284.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The implication is clear that", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "291.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it used to be alive, now it is dead.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "296.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gautam Buddha does not talk about God at all.", 
            "dur": "4.359", 
            "start": "309.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is so irrelevant", 
            "dur": "3.201", 
            "start": "315.339"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that he does not pay any attention to the subject.", 
            "dur": "5.28", 
            "start": "319.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now to a Christian, or to a Hindu, or to a Mohammedan,", 
            "dur": "5.16", 
            "start": "328.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is impossible to conceive of a religion without God.", 
            "dur": "4.5", 
            "start": "336.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "God is the center of most of the religions.", 
            "dur": "6.1", 
            "start": "344.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Only three religions are free of God.", 
            "dur": "4.079", 
            "start": "351.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One is Gautam Buddha&#39;s,", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "358"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "another is Mahavira&#39;s,", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "361.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the third is Lao Tzu&#39;s.", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "364.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When for the first time Christian missionaries came in contact", 
            "dur": "4.5", 
            "start": "375"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with Buddhist scriptures they could not", 
            "dur": "2.959", 
            "start": "380.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "even conceive of the idea that a religion can be without a god.", 
            "dur": "5", 
            "start": "389"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What kind of religion will there be if there is no God?", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "400"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How are you going to pray? To whom?", 
            "dur": "2.901", 
            "start": "403.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who is going to send his prophets and his only begotten son?", 
            "dur": "6.279", 
            "start": "408.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who is going to send saviors for you?", 
            "dur": "2.861", 
            "start": "417.139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who is going to judge", 
            "dur": "2.941", 
            "start": "422.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "whether you are", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "428.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to be sent to hell or heaven?", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "432"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "God removed,", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "436.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hell and heaven are also removed.", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "439"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "God removed,", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "442.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "punishment and reward are also removed.", 
            "dur": "3.5", 
            "start": "445.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "God removed,", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "449.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the very idea of judgment is removed.", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "452"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then there is no sin,", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "461"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and no virtue.", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "464"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who will decide it?", 
            "dur": "1.462", 
            "start": "466.538"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And they were even more surprised", 
            "dur": "2.821", 
            "start": "475.818"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that Gautam Buddha is", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "481"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "known by his disciples --", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "485.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and now even by those who are not disciples --", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "490.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as Bhagwan Gautam Buddha.", 
            "dur": "2.65", 
            "start": "495.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now &#39;Bhagwan&#39; means God.", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "500.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This was very puzzling.", 
            "dur": "1.501", 
            "start": "505.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gautam Buddha does not believe in any God.", 
            "dur": "3.101", 
            "start": "508.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How did he even allow his disciples", 
            "dur": "4.45", 
            "start": "516"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to address him as Bhagwan?", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "522.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The same is the situation with Jainism.", 
            "dur": "3.941", 
            "start": "528.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They are even more strict", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "537.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about the absence of God.", 
            "dur": "2.551", 
            "start": "542.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Buddha simply ignores the whole subject.", 
            "dur": "3.86", 
            "start": "547.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is not worth any consideration.", 
            "dur": "3.3", 
            "start": "551.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Jainism does not leave it,", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "557.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because there is a danger", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "561"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the whole thing cropping up again,", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "563.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "once Mahavira is gone.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "567.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He wants it to be clearly stated that there is no God,", 
            "dur": "6.6", 
            "start": "571.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and there has never been any God,", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "578.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and there is no creation", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "582"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because there is no creator.", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "584"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is an evolving world.", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "587"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What Charles Darwin found", 
            "dur": "2.681", 
            "start": "590.539"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "two thousand years afterwards", 
            "dur": "2.821", 
            "start": "597.179"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was known to Mahavira, that it is not a creation,", 
            "dur": "4.82", 
            "start": "601.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is an evolving world.", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "606.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It has been forever here and will be forever here.", 
            "dur": "5.78", 
            "start": "611.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The whole concept of creation and a creator", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "618.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is just idiotic.", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "624.46"
        }, 
        {
